HEADWORD: Crownpiece
<hw>Crown"piece`</hw> <pr>(-p?s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A piece or part which passes over the head, as in a bridle.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A coin [In sense <sd>(b)</sd> properly <xex>crown
piece</xex>.] See <er>Crown</er>, 19.</def>⟦br⟧
